{{Quote|I still lived in an Incom company town, and even if you weren't interested in starfighters, they were still the basis of our economy and our culture.|[[Kell Tolkani]], in a letter to his parents reflecting on his life|<ref name="Naturalist">{{StoryCite|story=A Naturalist on Hoth|book=From a Certain Point of View: The Empire Strikes Back}}</ref>}}
'''Incom Corporation''' was a [[starship]] manufacturer whose designs included [[starfighter]]s, [[airspeeder]]s, and [[transport]]s.

==History==
In the [[High Republic Era]], the Incom Corporation manufactured [[starfighter]]s like the [[Z-24 Buzzbug]], the [[Z-28 Skywing]],<ref name="The High Republic: Light of the Jedi">''[[The High Republic: Light of the Jedi]]''</ref> and the [[Z-29 Skyhawk]].<ref name="The High Republic: The Rising Storm">''[[The High Republic: The Rising Storm]]''</ref> They later gained additional prominence during the last [[Standard year|years]] of the [[Galactic Republic]], developing the multi-purpose and durable [[Z-95 Headhunter]] starfighter<ref name="Tarkin">[[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']]</ref> in cooperation with the [[Sublights Products Corporation]] ("Subpro"). With the [[First Battle of Geonosis|outbreak]] of the [[Clone Wars]],<ref name="Encyclopedia">{{SWE|technology|z95headhunter|clone Z-95 starfighter}}</ref> Incom benefited from the instability brought on by the conflict<ref name="Naturalist" /> and produced vehicles for the [[Republic Navy]].<ref name="Encyclopedia" /> Even if the pilots who flew its craft died in great numbers during the fighting, Incom itself was able to reap the profits of the war.<ref name="Naturalist" /> It produced a [[Clone Z-95 starfighter|variant]] of the Z-95 that saw prolific use with the Republic Navy during the conflict,<ref name="Encyclopedia" /> as well as the [[Aggressive ReConnaissance-170 starfighter]], or ARC-170, which also saw service with the Republic.<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" />

Incom later went on to develop at least two [[airspeeder]] designs for both military and civilian use; the [[T-47 airspeeder]] that the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]] modified into "snowspeeders" on [[Hoth]], and the popular [[T-16 skyhopper]] was used by youths on many worlds.<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" />

[[File:Incom_UT-60D_-_SW_Show.png|thumb|left|250px|Incom's UT-60D]]
However, Incom's most notable product was the [[T-65B X-wing starfighter]] used by the Rebel Alliance.<ref name="X Encyclopedia">{{SWE|technology|xwing|X-wing starfighter}}</ref> Designed with the Z-95 and ARC-170 Clone Wars-era fighters in mind,<ref name="Xwing History">{{Databank|x-wing-fighter-history-gallery|X-wing Fighter History Gallery}}</ref> the venerable [[snub-fighter]], though initially in public use, was extensively fielded by the Rebel Alliance throughout the [[Galactic Civil War]] against the [[Galactic Empire]].<ref name="Lost Stars">''[[Lost Stars]]''</ref>

Shortly thereafter, Incom went go on to produce the [[UT-60D U-wing starfighter/support craft]], as well as a civilian counterpart, the [[BT-45D U-wing]]. However, along with many other corporations during this [[Imperial Era|period]], Incom was [[Imperialization|Imperialized]] in order to be directly administered by the Empire, thus cutting short the production lines of craft like the U-wing.<ref name="ROUVG" /> Despite this, by the [[time]] of the [[First Order]]'s rise to power, Incom had reformed into [[Incom-FreiTek Corporation]], which went on to produce the [[T-70 X-wing starfighter|T-70]] and the [[T-85 X-wing starfighter|T-85 X-wing]] fighters.<ref name="Cross">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: Incredible Cross-Sections]]''</ref><ref name="Before">''[[Before the Awakening]]''</ref>

